<doc id="451648" wikidata="Q4934987" url="?curid=451648" title="Bobby F. England">
<text>Bobby F. England (born May 13, 1932) is an American former politician. A Democrat, he was a member of the North Carolina General Assembly representing the state&#x27;s 112th House district, including constituents in Cleveland and Rutherford counties. He was born in Spindale, North Carolina.

In 2009, England was credited with helping to save the life of fellow Rep. Becky Carney who suffered cardiac arrest at the state legislative building.

