<doc id="451702" wikidata="Q6551585" url="?curid=451702" title="Linda Garrou">
<text>Linda Garrou (January 17, 1943 – March 19, 2022) was a Democratic member of the North Carolina General Assembly representing the state&#x27;s thirty-second Senate district since 1999 until 2012. Her district includes constituents in Forsyth county. An administrator from Winston-Salem, North Carolina, Garrou was the Co-Chair of the Senate Appropriations/Base Committee, and the Pensions, Retirement and Aging Committee.

Garrou died on March 19, 2022, at Forsyth Memorial Hospital, in Winston-Salem, North Carolina.

